<section sectnbr = "5A">
<servcat sctnbr = "05" scnbr = "01">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70B5106009" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "03" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Shift Lock Solenoid Inspection
</title>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Reverse connection of the polarity may damage the shift lock solenoid.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove console box. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B9806012"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect select lever connector (1).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check that shift lock solenoid rod moves smoothly and returns when positive terminal of battery is connected to terminal “5” and negative terminal of battery is connected to terminal “10”.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Replace select lever assembly, if solenoid rod does not move smoothly.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A510024.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "95.409mm" ver = "02" gw = "195" gh = "254"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
